er came to power, reflection by a leading intellectual on contemporary culture and events, and the closest thing we have to a memoir by the boy from Lublin, Poland, who became one of the finest poets of the twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aJewish fiction. 0aJewsvFiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aDeshell, Maier, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuterman, Norbert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWisse, Ruth R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWisse, Ruth, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030009514240uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030016878540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300168785423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300168785/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY